body:
No real need for me to make a Watson api handler. You just make a ToneAnalyzerV3 object and 
```javascript
var toneParams = {
  tone_input: { 'text': {your text here},
  content_type: 'application/json'
};
```
and then call
```javascript
toneAnalyzer.tone(toneParams, {your return function})
```
Ex:
```javascript
toneAnalyzer.tone(toneParams, function (error, toneAnalysis) {
  if (error) {
    console.log(error);
  } else {
    console.log(JSON.stringify(toneAnalysis, null, 2));
  }
});
```
Then the data in tone analysis is formatted like 
```javascript
